{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "name": "Southern white-faced owl", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-ptilopsis", "name": "Ptilopsis", "latinName": "Ptilopsis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Ptilopsis（Ptilopsis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联2种鸟类，如白臉角鴞、Southern white-faced owl。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 2, "x": 522.29, "y": -171.25, "z": -2.89}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "name": "Southern white-faced owl", "latinName": "Ptilopsis granti", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Southern white-faced owl（Ptilopsis granti）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Southern white-faced owl。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -176.19, "y": -222.31, "z": -496.43}, {"id": "bird-southern-white-faced-owl-c71125dd", "name": "Southern white-faced owl", "englishName": "Southern white-faced owl", "latinName": "Ptilopsis granti", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The Southern white-faced owl (Ptilopsis granti) is a fairly small owl in the family Strigidae. It is native to the southern half of Africa. It was formerly regarded as a subspecies of the northern white-faced owl (P. leucopsis) but the two are now commonly treated as separate species. Description It is 22–28 cm (8.7–11.0 in) long and weighs 185–220 g (6.5–7.8 oz). The upperparts are grey with dark streaks and there are white spots on the scapular feathers. The underparts are whitish with dark streaks. The face is white with a black border and black around the large orange eyes. The head has two short ear-tufts with black tips. Juvenile birds have a greyish face. The northern white-faced owl is usually paler and browner with reduced streaking below. Their call is a series of fast, bubbling hoots, uttered at night and frequently repeated. These fast, staccato notes followed by a longer and higher-pitched 'hoot' are extensively used during breeding season and pairs of owls often sing together. The Northern white-faced owl has a very different two-note call. Distribution Southern white-faced owls occur patchily in the western regions central and southern Africa, including Gabon, Republic of Congo, Democratic Republic of the Congo and Angola. They seem to be more common in regions such as Uganda, southern Kenya and Tanzania, as well as Zambia, Namibia, Botswana, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Eswatini and the northern regions of South Africa. Habitat and diet It inhabits savanna and dry woodland. It is usually seen alone or in pairs. It mainly hunts large insects, as well as occasional small mammals, birds and reptiles. Nesting The eggs are usually laid in the old nest of another bird. The clutch contains two or three eggs which are incubated for about 30 days. The young birds leave the nest about a month after hatching. Temperature adaptability After the summer, southern white-faced owls increase their resting metabolic rate by approximately 45% to adjust to the climate changes. Furthermore, the owls do this to increase cold temperature tolerance which is unusual for these creatures. Not only that, but the BMR (Basal Metabolic Rate) of the owl is lower than what is expected of other birds of a similar size to help them when there is a lack of food. This is unusual considering the lack of food and other survival resources during the winter. References Sinclair, Ian & Ryan, Peter (2003) Birds of Africa south of the Sahara, Struik, Cape Town. World Owl Trust (2005) Southern White-faced Owl. Accessed 19/09/07. Zimmerman, Dale A.; Turner, Donald A. & Pearson, David J. (1999) Birds of Kenya & Northern Tanzania, Christopher Helm, London. External links BirdLife species factsheet for Ptilopsis granti. (Southern) White-faced Owl - Species text in The Atlas of Southern African Birds. Data related to Ptilopsis granti at Wikispecies", "shortSummary": "The Southern white-faced owl (Ptilopsis granti) is a fairly small owl in the family Strigidae. It is native to the southern half of Africa.", "habitats": ["稀树草原"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Southern_white_faced_scops_owl.jpg/960px-Southern_white_faced_scops_owl.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-ptilopsis", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-ptilopsis", "species": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti"}, "expandable": true, "x": -176.19, "y": -222.31, "z": -490.31}], "links": [{"key": "bird-southern-white-faced-owl-c71125dd__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "source": "bird-southern-white-faced-owl-c71125dd", "target": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-ptilopsis", "source": "taxonomy-species-ptilopsis-granti", "target": "taxonomy-genus-ptilopsis", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Southern white-faced owl 属于属 Ptilopsis。"}]}
